00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
According to Aristotle, objects all fall at a constant speed, and that speed depends

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:09.000
on their weight, and when Aristotle says "constant speed," what he means is that

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:14.000
the instant you release the ball, it's already traveling at the same speed that it will hit the ground.

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:19.000
Okay. So, objects fall at constant speed and that speed is proportional to the mass.

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:22.000
